{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix redundant computation in pdcch_llr function indexing\n\n### Summary\nThe `pdcch_llr` function in the LTE UE PDCCH processing chain had inconsistent indexing calculations that resulted in redundant computations and potential data gaps. The function was using a formula `&pdcch_llr[2*symbol*frame_parms->N_RB_DL*12]` to calculate offsets, which didn't match the actual number of elements processed per symbol.\n\nThis caused:\n- For symbol 0: processes 16*N_RB_DL elements starting at offset 0 (correct)\n- For symbol 1: processes 24*N_RB_DL elements starting at offset 24*N_RB_DL (incorrect - creates an 8*N_RB_DL gap)\n\nThe fix implements proper offset calculation based on the actual elements processed per symbol:\n- Symbol 0: offset = 0, elements = 16*N_RB_DL\n- Symbol 1: offset = 16*N_RB_DL, elements = 24*N_RB_DL\n- Symbol 2: offset = 40*N_RB_DL, elements = 24*N_RB_DL\n- And so on...\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/LTE_UE_TRANSPORT/dci_ue.c`: Fixed indexing logic in `pdcch_llr` function to eliminate redundant computation and ensure consistent data placement.\n\n"
}